Conditional statements:to make the set of instructions execute when only the given condition is true
They are used to decide whether code is executed or not.it is executed in the sequence.
Block of code: set of instructions
It will execute only when that specific condition is true
Condition:an expression that evaluates in an result(true or false)
Methods:
If-only 1 possible condition.if the condition is true it will execute otherwise it will skip
Syntax:
if(condition){
--block of code
}
Example:
let a=5;
        let b=10;
        if(a<b){
            document.write("hi naavss","<br>")
        }
        document.write("welcome to india")
Output:
hi naavss
welcome to india
Else:
Example:

 let a=5;
        let b=10;
        if(a>b){
            document.write("hi naavss","<br>")
        }else{
            document.write("megh","<br>")
        }
        document.write("welcome to india")
Output:
megh
welcome to india

Ifelse
Else if:
Example:
 age=prompt("enter your age?")
       name=prompt("enter your name?")
       if (age<18){
        alert(name+ "u are too young to marry")
       }else if(age>35){
        alert(name+ "u are too old to marry")
       }else{
        alert(name+ "perfect age to marry")
       }

